abstract: Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
snippet: Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
headline_main: Jordan, Egypt Faulted for Deaths of US-Trained Sniffer Dogs
headline_print_headline: Jordan, Egypt Faulted for Deaths of US-Trained Sniffer Dogs

abstract: Britain’s Prince Charles has chosen an Associated Press photo taken on his historic trip to Cuba for his Christmas card.

abstract: The 1956 musical drama, with an acclaimed operatic score, will premiere this summer at Bard SummerScape in Annandale-on-Hudson.
snippet: The 1956 musical drama, with an acclaimed operatic score, will premiere this summer at Bard SummerScape in Annandale-on-Hudson.
lead_paragraph: Daniel Fish, the director behind the Tony Award-winning “Oklahoma!” revival, has a new midcentury musical reinvention project in the works: Frank Loesser’s acclaimed, quasi-operatic “The Most Happy Fella.”

abstract: The Kansas vs. Villanova rivalry has become glorious to view for college hoops fans. The two championship programs are intertwined, as much as nonconference teams can be, since the start of the century. Through snowstorms and court stormings, NCAA championship runs and a father-son connection this season, the Jayhawks and Wildcats have experienced many memorable moments.

lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — The Kansas vs. Villanova rivalry has become glorious to view for college hoops fans. The two championship programs are intertwined, as much as nonconference teams can be, since the start of the century. Through snowstorms and court stormings, NCAA championship runs and a father-son connection this season, the Jayhawks and Wildcats have experienced many memorable moments.

abstract: Feeling a little spent? Let Alison Roman’s skillet chicken with white beans, a one-pan shrimp scampi, and a lemony carrot soup power you through the holidays.
snippet: Feeling a little spent? Let Alison Roman’s skillet chicken with white beans, a one-pan shrimp scampi, and a lemony carrot soup power you through the holidays.
lead_paragraph: Hi and welcome to Five Weeknight Dishes. Are you feeling a little spent, a little stuffy, a little too ready to relax this Christmas? I’ve been under the weather, not gravely so, but I am going through tissues at a maniacal pace, rewatching “The Crown,” and then Googling the royal family on my phone. (I believe this is called “self-care.”)

abstract: A cruise ship scraped another while trying to dock in the Mexican Caribbean resort of Cozumel on Friday, damaging at least one of the boats and resulting in minor injuries to six passengers.
snippet: A cruise ship scraped another while trying to dock in the Mexican Caribbean resort of Cozumel on Friday, damaging at least one of the boats and resulting in minor injuries to six passengers.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — A cruise ship scraped another while trying to dock in the Mexican Caribbean resort of Cozumel on Friday, damaging at least one of the boats and resulting in minor injuries to six passengers.
headline_main: 6 Hurt in Carnival Cruise Ships Accident at Mexico's Cozumel
headline_print_headline: 6 Hurt in Carnival Cruise Ships Accident at Mexico's Cozumel

abstract: An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
snippet: An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
lead_paragraph: CLEVELAND — An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
headline_main: Judge Upholds Firing of Police Officer Who Killed Tamir Rice
headline_print_headline: Judge Upholds Firing of Police Officer Who Killed Tamir Rice
